ster, NY|ssrn=2143034}}</ref>\n* Brenner, Galai & Sade. (2009). Sovereign debt auctions: uniform or discriminatory? [[Journal of Monetary Economics|Journal of monetary economics]], 56(2), 267-274.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Brenner|first=Menachem|last2=Galai|first2=Dan|last3=Sade|first3=Orly|date=2009-03-01|title=Sovereign Debt Auctions: Uniform or Discriminatory?|language=en|location=Rochester, NY|ssrn=1394962}}</ref>\n* Galili & Sade. (2006). \"The ostrich effect\" and the relationship between the liquidity and the yields of financial assets. [[The Journal of Business|The journal of business]], 79(5).<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Galai|first=Dan|last2=Sade|first2=Orly|date=2003-07-01|title=The 'Ostrich Effect' and the Relationship between the Liquidity and the Yields of Financial Assets|language=en|location=Rochester, NY|ssrn=431180}}</ref>\n* Schnitzlein, Zender & Sade. (2006). When less (potential demand) is more (revenue): asymmetric bidding capacities in feasible good auctions. [[The review of finance (rof)|The review of finance]] (ROF), 10(3), 389-416.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sade|first=Orly|last2=Schnitzlein|first2=Charles R.|last3=Zender|first3=Jaime F.|date=2005-05-10|title=When Less (Potential Demand) is More (Revenue): Asymmetric Bidding Capacities in Divisible Good Auctions|language=en|location=Rochester, NY|ssrn=705901}}</ref>\n* Schnitzlein, Zender & Sade. (2006). Competition and cooperation in feasible good auctions: an experimental examination. [[The Review of Financial Studies|The review of financial studies]] (RFS), 19(1), 195-235.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sade|first=Orly|last2=Schnitzlein|first2=Charles R.|last3=Zender|first3=Jaime F.|date=2008-02-29|title=Competition and Cooperation in Divisible Good Auctions: An Experimental Examination|language=en|location=Rochester, NY|ssrn=900710}}</ref>\n* Kalay, Wohl & Sade. (2004). measuring stock illiquidity: an investigation of the demand and supply schedule at the TASE. [[The journal of financial economics]], 74(3), 461-486.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Kalay|first=Avner|last2=Sade|first2=Orly|last3=Wohl|first3=Avi|date=2005-02-17|title=Measuring Stock Illiquidity: An Investigation of the Demand and Supply Schedules at the TASE|language=en|location=Rochester, NY|ssrn=668061}}</ref>\n* Crowley & Sade. (2004). Does the option to cancel an order in a double auction market matter? [[The economics letters]], 83(1), 89-97.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Crowley|first=Steve|last2=Sade|first2=Orly|date=2005-02-16|title=Does The Option to Cancel an Order in a Double Auction Market Matter?|language=en|location=Rochester, NY|ssrn=667742}}</ref>\n* Brenner, Galili & Sade. (2010). A Note on Sovereign Debt Auctions: Uniform or discriminatory? In R. W. Kolb, J. Wiley & Sons, Inc., Sovereign Debt: From Safety to Default (119-127). New Jersey: [[John Wiley & Sons]], Inc.<ref name=\"In Books\">{{Cite web|url=http://orly-sade.huji.ac.il/?q=node/12|title=In Books|website=orly-sade.huji.ac.il|language=en|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n*Brenner, M., Galai, D. & Sade, O. (2016) Uniform or Discriminatory Auctions: Endogenizing Bidder\u2019s Choice in Divisible Good Auctions In ''Behavioral Finance: Where do Investors Biases Come From\"?'' edited by Itzhak Venezia.<ref name=\"In Books\" />\n*Zur, E. & Sade, O. (2011). Baseball and the art of fair value: Do managers or the prediction markets make better predictions? In I. Venezia & Z. Wiener., ''Bridging the GAAP: Recent advanced in finance and accounting'' (63-93). Singapore: World Scientific Publishing Co. Pte. Ltd.<ref name=\"In Books\" />\n\n== Books ==\nSade co-authored a children book that teaches young people some of the basics of [[economics]]:<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.calcalist.co.il/money/articles/0,7340,L-3537946,00.html|title=\u05d0\u05d9\u05e4\u05d4 \u05d2\u05d3\u05dc \u05d4\u05db\u05e1\u05e3? \u05e1\u05e4\u05e8\u05d9 \u05d4\u05d9\u05dc\u05d3\u05d9\u05dd \u05dc\u05d0 \u05de\u05de\u05e9 \u05e2\u05d5\u05e0\u05d9\u05dd|date=2011-10-09|work=\u05db\u05dc\u05db\u05dc\u05d9\u05e1\u05d8 - www.calcalist.co.il|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\n\u2022    Sade, O. & Neurborne, E. (2011). How Ella Grew An Electric Guitar. New York: [[CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform]] (110 Pages)\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://orly-sade.huji.ac.il/ Official Website]\n* [http://orly-sade.huji.ac.il/?q=node/30 Orly Sade's CV 2018 at her website]\n* [http://bschool.huji.ac.il/en/Faculty_%26amp%3B_Research/Orly_Sade Personal Profile at the HUJI website]\n* [http://www.stern.nyu.edu/faculty/bio/orly-sade Personal Profile at the NYC website]\n* [http://www.israelemb.org/washington/Speakers-Guide/Business/Pages/Orly-Sade.aspx Sade's page at the website of The Embassy of Israel to the U.S]\n* [http://www.isa.gov.il/sites/ISAEng/ABOUT/Commissioners%20of%20the%20ISA/Pages/Prof--Orly-Sade.aspx Sade's Page at the ISA website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sade, Orly}}\n[[Category:Hebrew University of Jerusalem faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Utah alumni]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tel Aviv University alumni]]\n[[Category:Israeli women academics]]\n[[Category:21st-century economists]]\n[[Category:20th-century economists]]\n[[Category:Experimental economists]]\n[[Category:Israeli economists]]\n[[Category:Israeli women economists]]\n", "text_old": "'''Orly Sade''' or '''\u05d0\u05d5\u05e8\u05dc\u05d9 \u05e9\u05d3\u05d4''' (born 1969) is a financial economist based out of the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] who has been noted for her research regarding behavioral and experimental finance and crowdfunding platforms. Sade is the Israel [[Associate professor|Associate Professor]] of [[Finance]] at the Department of Finance, [[Jerusalem School of Business Administration|School of Business Administration]] at the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]]. She is the first female professor in the field of finance at Hebrew University.<ref>http://new.huji.ac.il/article/18295</ref>\n\n== Education and academic career ==\nSade has finished her [[Bachelor of Arts|BA degree]] in [[Business administration|Business Administration]] and [[Economics]] as well as her [[Master of Business Administration|MBA degree]] in Business Administration at the [[Tel Aviv University]], [[Israel]]. In 2001 she had finished her [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D]]. in Finance at the [[David Eccles School of Business]], [[University of Utah]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://orly-sade.huji.ac.il/?q=node/30|title=Academic Profile {{!}} Orly Sade (PhD)|website=orly-sade.huji.ac.il|language=en|access-date=2018-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.calcalist.co.il/markets/articles/0,7340,L-3610280,00.html|title=\u05d4\u05de\u05d5\u05e2\u05de\u05d3\u05ea \u05d4\u05de\u05d5\u05d1\u05d9\u05dc\u05d4 \u05dc\u05db\u05d9\u05e1\u05d0 \u05d4\u05de\u05e4\u05e7\u05d7 \u05e2\u05dc \u05d4\u05d1\u05d9\u05d8\u05d5\u05d7: \u05d0\u05d5\u05e8\u05dc\u05d9 \u05e9\u05d3\u05d4|date=2013-08-18|work=\u05db\u05dc\u05db\u05dc\u05d9\u05e1\u05d8 - www.calcalist.co.il|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\nSince 2013 Sade is an Associate Professor of Finance at the Department of Finance, School of Business Administration, Hebrew University of Jerusalemw, here she served as director of the BA program. She is the first woman in Israel to become an Associate Professor with tenure in the field of Finance.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://new.huji.ac.il/article/18295|title=\u05e4\u05e8\u05d5\u05e4' \u05d0\u05d5\u05e8\u05dc\u05d9 \u05e9\u05d3\u05d4 \u05d4\u05d9\u05d0 \u05d4\u05d0\u05d9\u05e9\u05d4 \u05d4\u05e8\u05d0\u05e9\u05d5\u05e0\u05d4 \u05d1\u05d0\u05e8\u05e5 \u05d4\u05d6\u05d5\u05db\u05d4 \u05d1\u05ea\u05d5\u05d0\u05e8 \u05e4\u05e8\u05d5\u05e4\u05e1\u05d5\u05e8 \u05dc\u05de\u05d9\u05de\u05d5\u05df {{!}} \u05d4\u05d0\u05d5\u05e0\u05d9\u05d1\u05e8\u05e1\u05d9\u05d8\u05d4 \u05d4\u05e2\u05d1\u05e8\u05d9\u05ea \u05d1\u05d9\u05e8\u05d5\u05e9\u05dc\u05d9\u05dd {{!}} The Hebrew University of Jerusalem|website=new.huji.ac.il|language=he|access-date=2018-04-17}}</ref>\n\nSade is a Visiting Associate Professor in the finance department at the [[New York University Stern School of Business|Stern School of Business]], [[New York University|NYU]]. In the past, she worked as a visiting Associate Professor in different universities such as [[IE Business School|IE]] in [[Madrid]], [[Einaudi Institute for Economics and Finance|EIEF]] in [[Rome]], [[New Economic School|NES]] in [[Moscow]] and at [[New York University Shanghai|NYU Shanghai]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stern.nyu.edu/faculty/bio/orly-sade|title=NYU Stern - Orly Sade - Visiting Associate Professor of Finance|website=www.stern.nyu.edu|language=en|access-date=2018-04-17}}</ref> Sade is an experimental economist based at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, Israel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.scidev.net/global/funding/feature/the-advent-of-crowdfunding-innovations-for-development.html|title=The advent of crowdfunding innovations for development|last=SciDev.Net|work=SciDev.Net|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en}}</ref> Sade has been noted for her research with Dan Marom regarding crowdfunding platforms.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://nocamels.com/2014/09/women-entrepreneurs-are-more-successful-than-men-in-crowdfunding-campaigns/|title=Women Entrepreneurs Are More Successful Than Men In Crowdfunding Campaigns|date=2014-09-08|work=NoCamels - Israeli Innovation News|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/kickstarter-closes-the-funding-gap-for-women-1407949759|title=Kickstarter Closes the 'Funding Gap' for Women|last=Simon|first=Ruth|date=2014-08-13|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=2018-04-30|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.racked.com/2016/12/14/13871472/sexism-retail-investing|title=Why Female-Oriented Businesses Like Etsy and Thinx Struggle to Find Investors|work=Racked|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.calcalist.co.il/local/articles/0,7340,L-3639868,00.html|title=\u05d1\u05d3\u05e8\u05da \u05dc\u05de\u05d9\u05de\u05d5\u05df \u05d4\u05de\u05d5\u05e0\u05d9\u05dd, \u05d4\u05e6\u05d8\u05d9\u05d9\u05d3\u05d9 \u05d1\u05e0\u05e2\u05dc\u05d9 \u05d1\u05dc\u05d8|date=2014-09-04|work=\u05db\u05dc\u05db\u05dc\u05d9\u05e1\u05d8 - www.calcalist.co.il|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref> She is the first female professor in the field of finance at Hebrew University.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.calcalist.co.il/markets/articles/0,7340,L-3707663,00.html|title=\u05d7\"\u05db \u05dc\u05e9\u05e2\u05d1\u05e8 \u05e8\u05d7\u05dc \u05d0\u05d3\u05d8\u05d5 \u05d5\u05e4\u05e8\u05d5\u05e4' \u05d0\u05d5\u05e8\u05dc\u05d9 \u05e9\u05d3\u05d4 \u05d9\u05de\u05d5\u05e0\u05d5 \u05dc\u05d3\u05d7\"\u05e6\u05d9\u05d5\u05ea \u05d1\u05db\u05dc\u05dc|date=2017-02-13|work=\u05db\u05dc\u05db\u05dc\u05d9\u05e1\u05d8 - www.calcalist.co.il|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\n== Other Work ==\nBesides her academic work, Sade, advises financial institutions and companies in the fields of finance, debt offerings, and tenders. Since 2017  Sade is a Director at \"[[Clal Insurance company]]\".\n\nIn the past, Sade worked in the Banking Supervision Department of the [[Bank of Israel]] and was a member of the advisory board of the Israeli [[Finance minister|Ministry of Finance]] as well as the board of directors of the [[Israel Securities Authority|Israeli Securities Authority.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.isa.gov.il/sites/ISAEng/ABOUT/Commissioners%20of%20the%20ISA/Pages/Prof--Orly-Sade.aspx|title=ISA :: Prof. Orly Sade|website=www.isa.gov.il|language=he-IL|access-date=2018-04-17}}</ref> Sade also served as a member of the investment committee for the \u201c[[Hadassah Medical Center|Hadassah]]\u201d [[pension fund]] and the Investment Committee of the Hebrew University Workers Fund. Sade was a member of the board of directors of the Hebrew University provident fund and an outside director at [[Sigma Mutual Funds]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Research ==\nSade's main fields of research are [[Behavioral economics|behavioral]] and [[experimental finance]], [[Auction|financial auctions]] and [[market microstructure]]s, the design of [[financial market]]s as well as [[Crowdfunding]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bschool.huji.ac.il/en/Faculty_&amp;_Research/Orly_Sade|title=The Jerusalem School of Business Administration {{!}} Faculty & Research|website=bschool.huji.ac.il|access-date=2018-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.calcalist.co.il/local/articles/0,7340,L-3639888,00.html|title=\u05e8\u05e4\u05d5\u05e8\u05de\u05ea \u05d1\u05db\u05e8 \u05dc\u05d0 \u05ea\u05de\u05d9\u05d3 \u05d4\u05d5\u05e2\u05d9\u05dc\u05d4|date=2014-09-04|work=\u05db\u05dc\u05db\u05dc\u05d9\u05e1\u05d8 - www.calcalist.co.il|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref> Sade's research is published in scientific Journals and presented at conferences worldwide. Sade received academic grants and awards including multiple grants from the [[Israel Science Foundation]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.isf.org.il/#/studies/undefined/%D7%90%D7%95%D7%A8%D7%9C%D7%99%20%D7%A9%D7%93%D7%94/undefined|title=Israel Science Foundation (ISF)|last=T.N.G|first=Datascope|website=www.isf.org.il|access-date=2018-04-17}}</ref> as well as the Abe Gray awards from the President of the Hebrew University.<ref name=\":1\" /> Sade has conducted research into pensions and found that people with less financial knowledge are less likely to take advantage of their available options.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.themarker.com/markerweek/1.4529376|title=\u05d4\u05de\u05d9\u05dc\u05d9\u05d0\u05e8\u05d3\u05d9\u05dd \u05e9\u05dc\u05e0\u05d5 \u05ea\u05e7\u05d5\u05e2\u05d9\u05dd \u05d1\u05d4\u05e8 \u05d4\u05db\u05e1\u05e3|last=\u05e4\u05e8\u05e5|first=\u05e1\u05de\u05d9|date=2017-10-20|work=TheMarker|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-5028435,00.html|title=\u05de\u05d5\u05d3\u05e2\u05d5\u05ea \u05dc\u05d6\u05db\u05d5\u05d9\u05d5\u05ea \u05e4\u05d9\u05e0\u05e0\u05e1\u05d9\u05d5\u05ea? \u05d1\u05e2\u05d9\u05e7\u05e8 \u05d1\u05e9\u05db\u05d1\u05d5\u05ea \u05d4\u05d7\u05d6\u05e7\u05d5\u05ea|last=\u05e8\u05d5\u05d6\u05e0\u05d1\u05e8\u05d2|first=\u05d0\u05dc\u05d9\u05e6\u05e4\u05df|date=2017-10-15|work=Ynet|access-date=2018-04-30|language=he}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.calcalist.co.il/money/articles/0,7340,L-3722793,00.html|title=\u05d1\u05e0\u05e7 \u05d9\u05e9\u05e8\u05d0\u05dc: \u05e8\u05e4\u05d5\u05e8\u05de\u05ea \u05d7\u05e9\u05d1\u05d5\u05e0\u05d5\u05ea \u05d4\u05d2\u05de\u05dc \u05d4\u05e7\u05d8\u05e0\u05d9\u05dd \u05d4\u05d9\u05d8\u05d9\u05d1\u05d4 \u05d9\u05d5\u05ea\u05e8 \u05dc\u05d0\u05d5\u05db\u05dc\u05d5\u05e1\u05d9\u05d5\u05ea \u05d7\u05d6\u05e7\u05d5\u05ea|date=2017-10-15|work=\u05db\u05dc\u05db\u05dc\u05d9\u05e1\u05d8 - www.calcalist.co.il|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref> She's also found that people with good finances check their financial options more often than those with poor finances, who tends to \"bury their heads in the sand.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globes.co.il/news/article.aspx?did=1000818298#|title=\u05e2\u05d5\u05d1\u05d3\u05d9\u05dd \u05e2\u05dc \u05e2\u05e6\u05de\u05e0\u05d5: \u05de\u05d3\u05d5\u05e2 \u05d0\u05e0\u05d5 \u05de\u05d3\u05d7\u05d9\u05e7\u05d9\u05dd \u05d0\u05ea \u05d7\u05d9\u05d9\u05e0\u05d5 \u05d4\u05db\u05dc\u05db\u05dc\u05d9\u05d9\u05dd?|last=\u05d5\u05d9\u05e0\u05e8\u05d1|first=\u05d2\u05dc\u05d9|website=Globes|language=he|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.themarker.com/law/1.1816286|title=\u05de\u05d5\u05db\u05e8\u05d9\u05dd \u05de\u05e0\u05d9\u05d5\u05ea \u05d1\u05e8\u05d5\u05d5\u05d7 \u05db\u05d3\u05d9 \u05dc\u05e8\u05d5\u05e5 \u05dc\u05e1\u05e4\u05e8 \u05dc\u05d7\u05d1\u05e8'\u05d4, \u05d0\u05d1\u05dc \u05dc\u05d0 \u05de\u05d5\u05db\u05e8\u05d9\u05dd \u05d1\u05d4\u05e4\u05e1\u05d3|last=\u05e8\u05d6|first=\u05d4\u05d9\u05dc\u05d4|date=2012-09-04|work=TheMarker|access-date=2018-04-30}}</ref>\n\n== Main Publications ==\n\n* Hurwitz, A., Sade, O. & Winter, E. (2020) Can Mandatory Minimum Annuity Laws Have Unintended Consequences? An Experimental Study. ''Journal of Economic Behavior & Organization,'' Volume 169, pp. 208-222.<ref>{{\u05e6-\u05de\u05d0\u05de\u05e8|\u05e9\u05dd=Unintended consequences of minimum annuity laws: An experimental study|\u05e7\u05d9\u05e9\u05d5\u05e8=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S016726811930352X|\u05db\u05ea\u05d1 \u05e2\u05ea=Journal of Economic Behavior & Organization|\u05e9\u05e0\u05ea \u05d4\u05d5\u05e6\u05d0\u05d4=2020-01-01|\u05e2\u05de=208\u2013222|\u05db\u05e8\u05da=169|doi=10.1016/j.jebo.2019.11.008|\u05de\u05d7\u05d1\u05e8=Abigail Hurwitz, Orly Sade, Eyal Winter}}</ref>\n* Hurwitz, A. & Sade, O. (2019) An Investigation of Time Preferences, Life Expectancy and Annuity versus Lump-Sum Choices \u2013 Can Smoking Harm Long-Term Saving Decisions? ''Journal of Economic Behavior & Organization,'' online edition.<ref>{{\u05e6-\u05de\u05d0\u05de\u05e8|\u05e9\u05dd=An investigation of time preferences, life expectancy, and annuity versus lump sum choices: Can smoking harm long-term saving decisions?|\u05e7\u05d9\u05e9\u05d5\u05e8=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0167268119301507|\u05db\u05ea\u05d1 \u05e2\u05ea=Journal of Economic Behavior & Organization|\u05e9\u05e0\u05ea \u05d4\u05d5\u05e6\u05d0\u05d4=2019-05-22|doi=10.1016/j.jebo.2019.05.011|\u05de\u05d7\u05d1\u05e8=Abigail Hurwitz, Orly Sade}}</ref>\n\n*Gafni, Marom & Sade. (2018) Are the Life and Death of an Early Stage Venture Indeed in the Power of the Tongue? Lessons from Online Crowdfunding Pitches. ''Strategic Entrepreneurship Journal (SEJ), 2018, pp. 1-21.''<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sade|first=Orly|last2=Marom|first2=Dan|last3=Gafni|first3=Hadar|date=2017-02-27|title=Are the Life and Death of an Early Stage Venture Indeed in the Power of the Tongue ? Le